<!-- Interview Tips -->
<section class="interview-tips">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header">
            <h2>Interview Success Strategies</h2>
            <p>Expert advice to help you prepare for and excel in your next interview</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tips-container">
            <div class="tip-card">
                <div class="tip-header">
                    <div class="tip-number">1</div>
                    <h3>Research Thoroughly</h3>
                </div>
                <p>Go beyond the company website. Understand their recent news, products, competitors, and industry position. Check employee reviews on Glassdoor and understand their culture.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-card">
                <div class="tip-header">
                    <div class="tip-number">2</div>
                    <h3>Prepare Your Stories</h3>
                </div>
                <p>Develop 5-7 accomplishment stories using the STAR method (Situation, Task, Action, Result). Quantify your achievements with numbers, percentages, and timeframes.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-card">
                <div class="tip-header">
                    <div class="tip-number">3</div>
                    <h3>Practice Aloud</h3>
                </div>
                <p>Rehearse your answers out loud, not just in your head. Record yourself to check for clarity, pace, and filler words. Practice with a friend for feedback.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-card">
                <div class="tip-header">
                    <div class="tip-number">4</div>
                    <h3>Prepare Questions</h3>
                </div>
                <p>Develop insightful questions that show your understanding of the role and company. Ask about challenges, success metrics, team dynamics, and growth opportunities.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-card">
                <div class="tip-header">
                    <div class="tip-number">5</div>
                    <h3>Technical Preparation</h3>
                </div>
                <p>Review technical concepts relevant to your field. Practice coding problems, case studies, or presentations. Be ready to explain your thought process, not just solutions.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-card">
                <div class="tip-header">
                    <div class="tip-number">6</div>
                    <h3>Follow Up Effectively</h3>
                </div>
                <p>Send personalized thank-you emails within 24 hours. Reference specific discussion points to show your engagement. Reiterate your interest and fit for the position.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

